According to Dr. Syzygium Aromaticum, as of 21:19 on March 17, there were 9,084 confirmed cases in China, bringing the total to 81,335, including 143 imported cases. There were 2830 severe cases, 3231 death cases and 68820 cured cases.

Outside China, there are 88,544 confirmed cases, 104676 confirmed cases, 4,191 deaths and 11,941 cures. At least 140 countries have confirmed cases of new coronary pneumonia outside China.

Development of epidemic situation

More than 100,000 cases have been confirmed outside China. As of 7:00 a.m. Beijing Time on March 17, the cumulative number of confirmed cases outside China had exceeded 100,000, according to real time epidemic data released by the Johns Hopkins University, italy, Iran, Spain, South Korea, Germany and France have confirmed 27,980,14,991,9,942,8,320,7,272 and 6,650 cases, respectively, of spread to the Arctic Greenland. On March 16, France declared a "state of war" . As of the 17th, the countries imposing the blockade include Italy, Spain, the Czech Republic, Venezuela, Kyrgyzstan, Colombia, Honduras and so on.

Imported cases spread to more than provinces, with the largest number returning from Spain. From 0 to 24 hours on March 16,20 new cases were reported from 8 provinces and cities, including Beijing (9 cases) , Shanghai (3 cases) , Guangdong (3 cases) , Zhejiang (1 case) , Shandong (1 case) , Guangxi (1 case) , Yunnan (1 case) and Shaanxi (1 case) . Among the imported countries, 7 cases were imported from Spain, 4 cases from the United Kingdom, 3 cases from the United States, 2 cases each from France and Italy, 1 case each from the Philippines and Indonesia. On March 17,3 cases were reported in Beijing, 1 in Guangxi, 1 in Sichuan and 1 in Yunnan.

On March 16, the National Health Commission said that "the import of external prevention has become the top priority in the prevention and control of the epidemic situation in China. ".

France enters "state of war" after EU plans 30-day closure. The president of the European Commission, jean-claude von Der Leyen, said she proposed a 30-day restriction on all non-essential travel to the EU. The proposal would not affect travel between EU countries, but some member states have taken a step in that direction. Ten of the 26 Schengen area countries have begun border controls.

French President Maqueron declared "we are at war" , banning public gatherings of any size starting with Tuesday and postponing the upcoming municipal elections. His orders amount to a national directive requiring people to stay at home except for basic needs. This is one of the strictest measures in Europe. He said people would be fined even if they met their friends on the street or in a park. The French Health Minister said the government requires each Frenchman to contact up to five people a day.

The Pentagon has 37 confirmed cases. Secretary of Defense Mark Esper and Deputy Secretary of Defense David Norquist will be quarantined to prevent a new outbreak, the Pentagon has announced. Starting March 16, the two top Pentagon officials will be in "physical isolation" , communicating with others only by video phone. The Ministry of defence will carefully screen access to the residence of the Minister of Defence and control the number of personnel. So far, the Pentagon has seen 37 newly diagnosed cases, including 18 military personnel.

Future Studies

The study found that children with mild new coronary symptoms are more likely to be missed. Contrary to the public's early impression that "children and young people are not susceptible to the new crown" , evidence suggests that infection in children has already occurred in the early stages of the new crown epidemic, according to a study published online March 12 in the leading International Medical Journal, The New England Journal of Medicine Pneumonia has infected at least six children between January 2 and 8,2020. Meanwhile, between December 8,2019, and February 6,2020, nine babies under the age of one were admitted to hospital, according to a paper by Wuhan University and his team, published Feb. 14 in the journal Jama. Many studies have shown that children are susceptible to the new coronavirus, and family-associated infection is the main cause. The symptoms of infection in children are generally mild, but not typical, and are easily overlooked and missed. Neglected infections in children may also be the source of family infections.

Urban Prevention and control

Xiaotangshan Hospital reopened in Beijing. The Xiaotangshan Hospital in Changping District has been reopened in Beijing since March 16, mainly for the treatment of those who need screening, suspected cases and mild and ordinary confirmed cases among those returning from overseas. When an incoming passenger is quarantined at the airport, he or she is considered to be at higher risk and is sent to the airport for treatment together with other mild cases. The hospital was originally built in seven days during the SARS outbreak in 2003, and has remained there for seven years. Since January 23,5,000 builders have been stationed in the building for renovation and 1,000 beds have been opened.

Beijing Municipal Education Commission: It is still not the time to consider starting school. Li Yi, a spokesman for the Beijing Municipal Education Commission, said on March 16 that in light of the current development of the epidemic, it is still not supportive of large-scale gatherings of people, and it is not time to consider the start of the school year. He hoped parents would not listen to rumors. According to the specific development of the epidemic at that time, the readiness of schools, as well as the situation in various regions, Li Yi said, the final formulation of an accurate and detailed start-up plan. "The start time in Beijing will still depend on the development of the epidemic. It will definitely be announced in advance to give schools, parents and students time to prepare. "

An average of 120,000 people enter the country every day, and many places have adopted quarantine policies. "On March 16, the State Council's Joint Defense and Joint Control Mechanism held a press conference, " said Liu Haitao, director of the border inspection and Management Department of the State Administration for Migration, "since March 11, when the World Health Organization declared the new coronavirus epidemic a global pandemic, an average of 120,000 people have entered the country at land, sea and air ports of entry. Of these, 20,000 people arrived on international flights per day, with foreigners accounting for about 10 per cent.". Advice to mainland residents on minimising travel arrangements.

Recently, local governments have adjusted their policies on segregation of immigrants. People entering through Beijing will be quarantined and will be sent to the Xinguo Exhibition, where vehicles from various provinces and cities will be sent to the quarantines for 14 days. Wuhan will also implement a policy of centralized isolation for all people entering the country. Shanghai has designated 16 key countries, including South Korea, Japan, Iran, Italy, France, Spain, Germany, the United States, the United Kingdom, Switzerland, Sweden, Belgium, Norway, the Netherlands, Denmark and Austria, visitors who have visited these countries in the past 14 days have requested concentration or home quarantine; the area listed as "yellow card" in Guangzhou is still South Korea, Japan, Iran and Italy.

Medical Solution

First clinical trial of a new coronavirus vaccine begins in the United States. On March 16, the National Institutes of Health said Biotechnology Company MODERNA inc. . The first human trials of an experimental vaccine against COVID-19 have begun. The first anonymous experimenter received the experimental vaccine at Kaiser Permanente in Seattle. Public Health officials say 45 young, healthy volunteers will be given different doses of the drug in clinical trials. All volunteers were not at risk because the reagent itself did not contain the virus, and the first phase of the trial was purely to verify the safety and side effects of the vaccine, accumulating data for a larger trial. Vaccine Trials can take as long as 18 months. At present, there are more than ten research institutions around the world are accelerating the development of related vaccines.

China's first new crown vaccine enters clinical trials nearly a month earlier than expected. On the morning of March 17,06185.HK  announced that the company, in collaboration with the Institute of Bioengineering of the Academy of Military Sciences, has developed a recombinant adenovirus vector for the COVID-19 vaccine and has submitted an application for pre-evaluation of the clinical trial of the new drug, and initiate pre-recruitment of healthy volunteers. "Most of the pre-clinical work, including animal efficacy and safety trials, has been completed on the first nine identified vaccine development tasks, " the official said, adding that most teams are expected to complete pre-clinical preparations and start applications and trials in April.

Peripheral influence

Shanghai's first case of underreporting sentenced. On March 16, the Shanghai Jinshan District People's Court publicly tried the case of Li mou-ping obstructing the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases. The defendant was sentenced to one year and three months'imprisonment, suspended for one year and six months, for obstructing the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases during the outbreak of new coronavirus. According to the circular, Li returned to Shanghai from Wuhan, concealing the trip, many times in and out of public places. Li Not only concealed Wuhan's travel history, but also had close contact with many medical staff during the treatment of cough and other symptoms. In the end, Li led to the isolation of 55 people he had close contact with, including 11 medical staff.

Euro 2012 is set to be postponed for another year. On March 17, the Norwegian Football Federation took the lead in tweeting that UEFA had decided to postpone the European Cup, which was due to start on June 12,2020, for a year and is now scheduled for 2021. UEFA will then communicate with FIFA. This year marks the 60th anniversary of the European Championship. The tournament was originally planned to take place in 11 countries and 12 cities across Europe without a host country.

The outlook for the economy has worsened, with U.S. stocks fusing for the third time this month. On the evening of March 16, the three major U.S. stock indexes opened lower, triggering the third fuse this month. S&P 500 is down 12% , its biggest percentage fall since the October 1987 crash, and has fallen nearly 30% since peaking last month. Major benchmarks in Asia, Europe and the US all fell on Monday.

According to China's statistics bureau, the country's industrial output in January and February fell by 13.5 percent in real terms from a year earlier, a record low, while private investment fell by 26.4 percent. In the US, the New York Fed's manufacturing index fell in March to its lowest level since 2009. The sell-off came in spite of extraordinary measures taken by the Federal Reserve on Sunday afternoon to boost the US economy. That suggests an economic crisis is unfolding as companies close and borders close. Given the apparent slowdown in economic activity, energy prices have fallen sharply. Global oil prices have fallen below $30 a barrel, their lowest level in more than four years.

The media attention

Will the Tokyo Olympics be postponed? According to the Japanese Sports magazine Nikkan Sports, several Tokyo organizing committees agreed to postpone the Games until 2022, so that the Tokyo Summer Games and the Beijing Tokyo Games would be held in the same year. The plan, proposed by Tokyo Olympic Organizing Committee member George Takahashi, will be discussed on the 30th of this month. But the ANBE administration still wants the games to go ahead, saying on March 16 that it had the "support" of other G7 leaders -- the US, UK, Germany, France, Italy and Russia -- via videoconference. The final decision on whether to postpone or cancel the Games in Tokyo is still in the hands of the International Olympic Committee.

Plague affects China's social consumption and retail sales. Retail sales of consumer goods totaled 5.213 billion yuan in the january-february period, down 20.5 percent in nominal terms from a year earlier (down 23.7 percent in real terms after adjusting for prices) , according to data released by the National Bureau of Statistics of the People's Republic of China on March 16. Of this total, retail sales of consumer goods other than automobiles totaled 4,847.6 billion yuan, down 18.9 percent.

From January to February, retail sales of consumer goods in urban areas totaled 4,488.1 billion yuan, down 20.7 percent year on year, and those in rural areas totaled 724.9 billion yuan, down 19.0 percent. In terms of consumption patterns, revenue from catering dropped 43.1 percent to 419.4 billion yuan in the first two months of 2020 compared with the same period last year, while retail sales dropped 17.6 percent to 4793.6 billion yuan.

In the same period, online retail sales nationwide totaled 1,371.2 billion yuan, down 3.0 percent year on year. Of this total, online retail sales of physical goods totaled 1,123.3 billion yuan, up 3.0 percent, accounting for 21.5 percent of the total retail sales of consumer goods. Among the online retail sales of physical goods, sales of food and consumer goods increased by 26.4 percent and 7.5 percent, respectively, while sales of wearing goods decreased by 18.1 percent.
